<p><strong><img class="alignleft" src="/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/R_Basu.jpg" alt=""/>Dr. Radha Basu, Chief Executive
        Officer, iMerit Technology Services </strong></p>
<p>Dr. Radha Basu is a leading tech and social enterprise entrepreneur and pioneer in the Indian software business. She
    is Founder and CEO of iMerit, and co-founder of Anudip Foundation &#8211; iMerit&#8217;s sister foundation.</p>
<p>
<div class="short_content_box">
    <div class="short_content"></p>
<p>Through iMerit and Anudip, Radha uses her experience in technology management to holistically address one of the
    world’s most pressing challenges &#8211; youth unemployment &#8211; while meeting the needs of global companies and
    NGOs. iMerit has employed hundreds of marginalized women and youth in digital and data services who contribute to
    growing industries ranging from virtual/augmented reality, to the sharing economy, to e-commerce and financial
    services.</p>
<p>Before founding iMerit and Anudip, Radha served as Chairman and CEO of SupportSoft, leading the company through
    initial and secondary public offerings in 2000 and 2003, and building it into a worldwide market leader in
    supporting automation software.
    Prior to SupportSoft, Radha spent 20 years at Hewlett Packard, most recently as Senior General Manager of the
    Electronic Business Software Organization, which she grew to a global $1.2 billion business. Radha&#8217;s career at
    HP began as she founded the company&#8217;s operations in India and set up the first software center of any
    multinational in Bangalore.</p>
<p>Radha currently sits on the boards of NetHope, Jhumki Basu Foundation, and the Miller Center for Social
    Entrepreneurship of Santa Clara University (SCU) and is Founder of the Frugal Innovation Lab of SCU.</p>
